# Heart Disease Prediction using Logistic Regression & Random Forest

## 📋 Project Overview
This project predicts whether a patient has heart disease based on clinical parameters like chest pain type, cholesterol levels, and maximum heart rate.

**Dataset:** Cleveland Heart Disease Database (303 samples, 13 features)

**Goal:** Binary classification (0 = No heart disease, 1 = Heart disease)

---

## 🎯 Results
| Model | Accuracy | Recall | F1-Score |
|-------|----------|--------|----------|
| Logistic Regression | 83.3% | 0.79 | 0.81 |



---

## 📊 Key Findings
- **Top 3 features:**
  1. Chest pain type (cp)
  2. Maximum heart rate (thalach)  
  3. ST depression (oldpeak)

- **Medical insight:** Chest pain type is the strongest predictor of heart disease


